issue.title: Uneven passwordFile/usernamePasswordFile support across services/objects
issue.body:
### Issue Summary:
Spinnaker services and objects have uneven support for passwordFile and usernamePasswordFile

The artifacts block only supports usernamePasswordFile,
https://docs.armory.io/armory-enterprise/installation/armory-operator/op-manifest-reference/artifact/#account-parameters-6

While the Concourse / Jenkins CI configs only support password:
https://docs.armory.io/armory-enterprise/installation/armory-operator/op-manifest-reference/ci/

As it stands, the latter's lack of passwordFile support requires users to store exposed passwords in git or store the config entirely (or the -local.yml variant) in vault instead of just the passwords alone.

### Cloud Provider(s):
Kubernetes

### Environment:
We utilize a K8S Spinnaker deployment, where clouddriver for example has a Vault init container that mounts a /vault/ directory that we set passwordFile (where available) to point to.

### Feature Area:
Igor / Clouddriver

### Description:
Expected:
Ability to use passwordFile evenly across services/objects.

Actual:
passwordFile is only supported in a few objects/services.

### Steps to Reproduce:
Configure a Spinnaker artifact to use passwordFile, it won't work.

### Additional Details:

issue.title: Re-order executions in waiting queue
issue.body:
### Feature Area:
Orca, Deck

### Description:
A requirement from the team we are working with is to have a re-shuffle option in the Spinnaker UI to change the order of the pipelines which are waiting on RUNNING executions

Please shout If anyone is also interested to discuss about this mini feature.

### Additional Details:
When having multiple items waiting there, which are arriving in timely order and running in FIFO order. However due to certain project urgencies, we quite often need to set a priority order of these Pipelines. Currently it's only possible by cancelling all the running pipelines and Re-run executions one after another in the right order

issue.title: CustomResource Not Showing as Available for Deletion in Delete or Patch Manifest Stage
issue.body:
### Issue Summary:
After adding Custom Resources via Halyard to Kubernetes accounts, the Custom Resource names do not show up in the drop down as available for deletion in either a Delete or Patch manifest type stage. 

### Cloud Provider(s):
Kubernetes

### Environment:
Spinnaker running in Kubernetes v1.23.7, version 1.26.6 of Spinnaker. Leveraging Halyard to deploy Spinnaker into the Kubernetes cluster. 

### Feature Area:
UI

### Description:
Clouddriver sees the custom resources and caches them properly, the appropriate Custom Resource Type is available in the drop down in the Patch Manifest or Delete Manifest type stages. But the name of the given Custom Resource does not show up as available in the drop down in the UI. 

The resource name can be entered manually and the Patch Manifest or Delete Manifest stage works appropriately. Presumably this is just a UI/Deck issue when listing the Custom Resource. 

Expected:

The name of the Custom Resource should be available in the drop down after adding the Custom resources to the Spinnaker Kubernetes account configuration to be selected for Delete or Patch

### Steps to Reproduce:
- Add Custom Resource of any Kind to Kubernetes Account in Spinnaker
- Create a pipeline with a Delete or Patch Manifest Stage
- Select Account, Namespace, Selector of Static Target, and Kind in the stage configuration
- The Name drop down will be empty when the Custom resource Kind is selected.

### Additional Details:

Screenshots of above:

Halyard Config:
![Screen Shot 2022-09-09 at 2 02 31 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/32780090/189415535-31abb8cf-34e2-468c-af73-0cc7217cfea3.png)

UI: 
[Screen Shot 2022-09-09 at 2.01.44 PM.pdf](https://github.com/spinnaker/spinnaker/files/9537797/Screen.Shot.2022-09-09.at.2.01.44.PM.pdf)

issue.title: Allow sensitive values to be used in preconfigured webhooks without showing up in the execution context
issue.body:
### Issue Summary:

Preconfigured webhooks may contain sensitive values (like credentials to authenticate with the webhook endpoint) with an expectation of privacy since those values are not displayed in Deck when adding the stage to a pipeline.  However, as mentioned [here](https://github.com/spinnaker/orca/pull/1329#issue-119663993) those values still are available in the execution context.  

### Feature Area: 

Webhook stages

### Description:

It would be helpful to be able to keep the values from the preconfigured webhook stage that aren't needed in Deck from being returned.   This could be the default behavior, but in cases where the values aren't sensitive it can be valuable to still have them available for troubleshooting.   Another option would be to allow the preconfigured stage to declare what values are sensitive:

```yaml
      customHeaders:
        X-Api-Key:
          - <newrelic-api-key>
        Content-Type:
          - application/json
      # Proposed change
      sensitiveHeaders:
        - X-Api-Key
      sensitivePayload: true
```
(I'm assuming that only headers or the payload would be expected to contain sensitive data)

### Additional details:

Relates to https://github.com/spinnaker/orca/pull/1329

issue.title: Option --assume-role not used in latest 'hal config storage s3 edit' command
issue.body:
### Issue Summary:
Option --assume-role not used in latest 'hal config storage s3 edit' command

### Cloud Provider(s):
S3

### Environment:
Local

### Feature Area:
Hal, config storage s3

### Description:
I want to use IAM role instead of --access-key-id to configure S3 storage. However, in hal command, only pass --assume-role doesn't work. Is there any way to configure IAM role for S3 storage with latest hal command?

### Steps to Reproduce:
```
hal config storage s3 edit --assume-role 'role/SpinnakerManaged' --region us-west-2
+ Get current deployment
  Success
+ Get persistent store
  Success
- Edit persistent store
  Failure
Validation in default.persistentStorage.s3:
! ERROR Failed to ensure the required bucket
  "xxxxxx" exists: Unable to execute HTTP request:
  Unexpected error: java.security.InvalidAlgorithmParameterException: the
  trustAnchors parameter must be non-empty
```

### Additional Details:
In https://github.com/spinnaker/halyard/blob/a036362b27581abeb83de99d682f0e200d12f1e1/halyard-cli/src/main/java/com/netflix/spinnaker/halyard/cli/command/v1/config/persistentStorage/s3/S3EditCommand.java
Variable assumeRole not used anywhere.

issue.title: Allow sensitive values to be used in preconfigured webhooks without showing up in the execution context
issue.body:
### Issue Summary:

Preconfigured webhooks may contain sensitive values (like credentials to authenticate with the webhook endpoint) with an expectation of privacy since those values are not displayed in Deck when adding the stage to a pipeline.  However, as mentioned [here](https://github.com/spinnaker/orca/pull/1329#issue-119663993) those values still are available in the execution context.  

### Feature Area: 

Webhook stages

### Description:

It would be helpful to be able to keep the values from the preconfigured webhook stage that aren't needed in Deck from being returned.   This could be the default behavior, but in cases where the values aren't sensitive it can be valuable to still have them available for troubleshooting.   Another option would be to allow the preconfigured stage to declare what values are sensitive:

```yaml
      customHeaders:
        X-Api-Key:
          - <newrelic-api-key>
        Content-Type:
          - application/json
      # Proposed change
      sensitiveHeaders:
        - X-Api-Key
      sensitivePayload: true
```
(I'm assuming that only headers or the payload would be expected to contain sensitive data)

### Additional details:

Relates to https://github.com/spinnaker/orca/pull/1329

issue.title: Uneven passwordFile/usernamePasswordFile support across services/objects
issue.body:
### Issue Summary:
Spinnaker services and objects have uneven support for passwordFile and usernamePasswordFile

The artifacts block only supports usernamePasswordFile,
https://docs.armory.io/armory-enterprise/installation/armory-operator/op-manifest-reference/artifact/#account-parameters-6

While the Concourse / Jenkins CI configs only support password:
https://docs.armory.io/armory-enterprise/installation/armory-operator/op-manifest-reference/ci/

As it stands, the latter's lack of passwordFile support requires users to store exposed passwords in git or store the config entirely (or the -local.yml variant) in vault instead of just the passwords alone.

### Cloud Provider(s):
Kubernetes

### Environment:
We utilize a K8S Spinnaker deployment, where clouddriver for example has a Vault init container that mounts a /vault/ directory that we set passwordFile (where available) to point to.

### Feature Area:
Igor / Clouddriver

### Description:
Expected:
Ability to use passwordFile evenly across services/objects.

Actual:
passwordFile is only supported in a few objects/services.

### Steps to Reproduce:
Configure a Spinnaker artifact to use passwordFile, it won't work.

### Additional Details:

issue.body:
### Issue Summary:
Option --assume-role not used in latest 'hal config storage s3 edit' command

### Cloud Provider(s):
S3

### Environment:
Local

### Feature Area:
Hal, config storage s3

### Description:
I want to use IAM role instead of --access-key-id to configure S3 storage. However, in hal command, only pass --assume-role doesn't work. Is there any way to configure IAM role for S3 storage with latest hal command?

### Steps to Reproduce:
```
hal config storage s3 edit --assume-role 'role/SpinnakerManaged' --region us-west-2
+ Get current deployment
  Success
+ Get persistent store
  Success
- Edit persistent store
  Failure
